# This file explains using Python in Jenkins by installing Python plugin

1. Install available Python plugin in Jenkins
     On the left pane of Jenkins nome page, go to "Manage Jenkins" --> "Manage plugins" --> "Available" tab and select "Python".
     
2. Restart Jenkins after successful installation.

3. To configure Python installations, step in Manage Jenkins > Configure System. Then look for the Python section.
     Python installed in your system will be auto-detected.
     To add new Python, click on "Add Python" and fill in required fiels.

4. Apply and Save these settings.
